sc ide: sc editor - improve automatic indentation

Align a line with the highest line above where *any* bracket is matched,
as opposed to the *first* bracket being matched.

This fixes the following case:

if(a, {
   b
},{
   c
})

sclang: allow trailing comma in message arguments and Event construction

This is now allowed:
(a:1, b:2,);
Pbind(\foo, 1, \bar, 2,);
obj.message(1, 2,)

plugins: MulAdd - generate only those ugens, which are actually supported

currently, MulAdd generates control-rate ugens, when in is control-rate,
although mul and add may be audio-rate. this breaks the following use
cases, which should yield silence.

({
	var sig = SinOsc.ar * 0.01;
	MulAdd(DC.kr(0), DC.kr(0), sig) - sig;
}.play)

({
	var sig = SinOsc.ar * 0.01;
	MulAdd(DC.kr(1), sig, DC.kr(0)) - sig;
}.play)

we avoid this by constructing only those MulAdd ugens, which are actually
supported.

Signed-off-by: Tim Blechmann <tim@klingt.org>

